{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-838790b2b5fc2b9c", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# MeanVC: Lightweight and Streaming Zero-Shot Voice Conversion via Mean Flows\narXiv: 2510.08392\nAuthors: Guobin Ma, Jixun Yao, Ziqian Ning, Yuepeng Jiang, Lingxin Xiong, Lei Xie, Pengcheng Zhu\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Introduction of a chunk-wise autoregressive denoising strategy in a diffusion transformer to combine the strengths of autoregressive and non-autoregressive paradigms for streaming processing.\n  2. Integration of mean flows to regress the average velocity field during training, enabling high-quality zero-shot voice conversion with a single sampling step.\n  3. Incorporation of diffusion adversarial post-training to mitigate over-smoothing and further enhance speech quality.\n  4. Demonstration of superior conversion quality, higher efficiency, and significantly lower latency compared to existing streaming zero-shot voice conversion systems while using only 14M parameters.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-NAR-Flow, TTS/控制-参考语音\n===\n# NouveauVoice: Generating Novel Pseudo Speakers for Voice Anonymization\narXiv: 2607.03985\nAuthors: Meiying Melissa Chen, Anastasia Kuznetsova, Zhenyu Wang, Zhiyao Duan\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "e45974bb-b816-4fcf-a9b3-335d4c1c9cf1", "uuid": "9ca84498-b977-4ab0-8d18-0412cfd6baf4", "timestamp": "2026-07-24T06:55:46.772Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# MeanVC: Lightweight and Streaming Zero-Shot Voice Conversion via Mean Flows\narXiv: 2510.08392\nAuthors: Guobin Ma, Jixun Yao, Ziqian Ning, Yuepeng Jiang, Lingxin Xiong, Lei Xie, Pengcheng Zhu\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Introduction of a chunk-wise autoregressive denoising strategy in a diffusion transformer to combine the strengths of autoregressive and non-autoregressive paradigms for streaming processing.\n  2. Integration of mean flows to regress the average velocity field during training, enabling high-quality zero-shot voice conversion with a single sampling step.\n  3. Incorporation of diffusion adversarial post-training to mitigate over-smoothing and further enhance speech quality.\n  4. Demonstration of superior conversion quality, higher efficiency, and significantly lower latency compared to existing streaming zero-shot voice conversion systems while using only 14M parameters.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-NAR-Flow, TTS/控制-参考语音\n===\n# NouveauVoice: Generating Novel Pseudo Speakers for Voice Anonymization\narXiv: 2607.03985\nAuthors: Meiying Melissa Chen, Anastasia Kuznetsova, Zhenyu Wang, Zhiyao Duan\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
